Reasoning: The paper deals with codes and their ability to recover from worst-case symbol deletions, which falls under the realm of information theory (cs.IT). The construction of codes and their efficiency for recovery suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The study of codes and their properties also has applications in complexity theory (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR).
